dict.string: An Alfred Workflow with dozens of features for Obsidian

tell application "Obsidian" to open location "obsidian://advanced-uri?commandid=workspace%253Anew-tab"
delay 0.2 # delay for detault new tab plugin
return "{query}"

if application "Obsidian" is not running then tell application "Obsidian" to activate delay 1.2 end if
tell application "Obsidian" to open location "obsidian://advanced-uri?commandid=quickadd%253ArunQuickAdd"
set parameter to do shell script "echo " & quoted form of (system attribute "parameter") & " | iconv -f UTF-8-MAC -t MACROMAN"
Search for External Links in your entire vault
tell application id "com.runningwithcrayons.Alfred" to set configuration "vault_path" to value "{query}" in workflow (system attribute "alfred_workflow_bundleid")

timestamp=`date '+%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M'` resolved_bkp_dest=~`echo -n $backup_location | sed -e "s/~//"` backup="$resolved_bkp_dest""/Obsidian-Backup_""$timestamp"".zip" vault=~`echo -n $vault_path | sed -e "s/~//"`
# directory change necessary to avoid zipping root folder # https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/245856/zip-a-file-without-including-the-parent-directory cd $vault zip -r --quiet $backup ./*
# restrict number of backups actual_number=$((max_number_of_bkps + 1)) cd $resolved_bkp_dest ls -t | tail -n +$actual_number | tr '\n' '\0' | xargs -0 rm
echo "$backup"

frontmost=$(osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" to get name of application processes whose frontmost is true and visible is true')
if [[ "$frontmost" == "Discord" ]] ; then echo "is true" else echo "is not true" fi
and Beta Plugins, if BRAT is installed
♋️ Open GitHub Repository of Beta Plugin

## 1️⃣ Setting up this workflow for the first time (required) 1. Install the Obsidian plugins [Advanced URI](https://obsidian.md/plugins?id=obsidian-advanced-uri) & [Metadata Extractor](https://obsidian.md/plugins?id=metadata-extractor). Enable both plugins. 2. Set your vault path in the configuration to the left. 3. Run the Alfred Command `osetup`. Obsidian will then restart.
---
## ⚙️ Workflow Configuration - **Some features require additional configuration to the left.** You can get further information on those features at the respective sections of the [documentation](https://github.com/chrisgrieser/shimmering-obsidian/blob/main/README.md). - To configure the hotkeys, double-click the [sky-blue fields](https://i.imgur.com/wlpht7f.png) at the top left of the workflow window.

save inputPath & empty query for next script Filter
Path to the vault that you want to control with this Alfred workflow.
Advanced users: If you use a different config folder than the default one.
Alfred keyword for the main search (Alfred-based Quick Switcher)
While enabled, all Notes with the cssclass "private" will be censored. This setting is meant to be enabled temporarily when sharing the screen.
Reduces the number of emojis used throughout the workflow. (This does not apply to emojis you have explicitly added yourself with the Supercharged Icons feature further below.)
Heading Levels to Ignore for the main search `o`. Example: `h4 h5 h6` will only show h1, h2 and h3.
When appending to a note (`fn + ↵`), the note will automatically be opened afterwards. Also applies to the Scratchpad feature.
When appending via `fn + ↵`, should the clipboard be appended or should there be a prompt for text to append
String to insert before content appended to a note via the Alfred-based Quick-Switchers (`fn + ↵`).
Merge Nested Tags for the tag-search `ot`. Example: `#inbox/to-read` and `#inbox/later` would both be subsumed under `#inbox`.

Vault-relative path to the template note to use when creating new notes with the `on` command or when browsing a folder via `o`. Any `{{title}}` placeholders in the template will be replaced with the name of the file. (Be aware that the template will be ignored when you use Folder Templates from the Templater Plugin.)
Vault-relative path to a folder where new notes created by `on` should be created. Leave empty to create the new note in the vault root.
To append/prepend icons to your search results, similar to the Supercharged Links Plugin. Consult the documentation for further information.
Vault-relative path to your Scratchpad Note. When you append `#foobar`, the text will be appended to the section with the heading "foobar".
String to insert before content appended to the Scratchpad.

Set language codes for Tesseract, e.g., `eng+deu` for English and German. You can find out the code for your language(s) here: https://tesseract-ocr.github.io/tessdoc/Data-Files-in-different-versions.html
String to insert before OCR'ed content.

Markdown file where the ORC'ed text will be saved to. When empty, will save/append to the file `{vault-path}/OCR-Screenshots.md`. Can be a markdown file outside your note and be used independently from Obsidian.
Folder where the image screenshots should be saved to. When empty, will save the images in `{vault-path}/screenshots/`.
Open mote after screenshot or OCR screenshot. (Disable this to be able to take screenshots in quick succession without opening Obsidian.)
Folder where the backups done by the `obackup` command should be saved. Recommended to be a folder outside your vault.

Must be an integer. Maximum number of backups that should be stored at the backup destination folder. When the number is reached, every new backup causes the oldest backup to be deleted. (Decrease this number, when your backup folder becomes too big.)
